Running all tests for project:

    from PROJECT_ROOT:
    	 (PROJECT_ROOT)$ python run_tests.py



Adding an testcase for a new intent:

    1. create a subclass mycity.test.intent_base_case.IntentBaseCase.

       These fields should be defined with the name of your intent 
       as it's identified in the MyCityController and on its title
       card. Indicate whether the intent has a reprompt response
       (ie., "Is there something else I can help you with") with
       the returns_reprompt_text flag

       test_example_intent.py

       from mycity.test.intent_base_case import IntentBaseCase


       class ExampleTestCase(IntentBaseCase): 
       
	     __test__ = True

	     intent_to_test = "ExampleIntent"
    	     returns_reprompt_text = False


    2. Add your TestCase to the test_cases list in run_tests.py. load_tests
    will pick up your TestCase and bundle it in the TestSuite run by executing 
    'python run_tests.py'.

    run_tests.py
    ...

    import mycity.test.test_example_intent as example
    ...

    TEST_CASES = [...,
		 example.ExampleTestCase,
		 ...
		 ]